Jordyn Woods...
Let's start with a couple of quotes:

Gammy, "As women, we've all let our little girl behavior get us into some grown woman mess."
.
.
Will, "This world is not going to break you. We won't allow it."
.
.
I watched the Red Table Talk and have so many emotions. First, THANK GOD she has the support of Jada & Will. I'm sure that many women can relate with me when I say that people can be cruel with their preconceived ideas about you when you're a young woman. Especially if you have a certain body type, wear makeup, like certain clothes, or, at times, for NO REASON AT ALL. They've just decided you're "fast" based on their preferred bias. I've been there and it's horrible.

Do I think she's lying? I don't know. 
But, I'm overwhelmed with joy that she is being covered and protected through this situation. I'm so grateful she has a platform to talk about her side of the story. She's young and made a mistake (her words). This doesn't mean she deserves the cloud of public humiliation that currently hangs over her head. 
Home wrecker? Nah. Naive and foolish? Yup. Deserving of a chance to move on with her life? Absolutely.

She's 21, y'all. Does anyone want to their mistakes from 10, 15+ years ago aired out and judged in the court of public opinion? I'll pass.
.
#redtabletalk #positivevibes #jordynwoods
